<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880121-0020 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: RJR Nabisco Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> RJR </CO><IN> TNM FOD TOB </IN><TEXT>   The Canadian unit of RJR Nabisco Inc., an Atlanta-based food and tobacco concern, said its Toronto holding company plans to acquire the unit's shares outstanding that it doesn't already own for 45 Canadian dollars each, or 180 million dollars ($140 million).    Nabisco Brands Ltd. of Toronto has 16 million shares outstanding, of which 12 million are owned by Nabisco Brands Investment Ltd., which is wholly owned by RJR Nabisco. Nabisco Brands Investment plans to make the offer for the remaining four million shares next week. The bid will be conditional on 90% of those shares being tendered.    In trading on the Toronto Stock Exchange yesterday, the Canadian unit's shares closed at 44 dollars, up eight dollars.    Nabisco Brands Investments said the transaction would allow it to achieve its business objectives more effectively. A company spokesman wasn't available to elaborate. </TEXT></DOC>